<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1940-07-10T09:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1940-07-10T09:00:00-05:00" n="746" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d746">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">125.283H3/126: Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Consul General at Casablanca</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Goold</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Casablanca</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1940-07-10T15:00:00+01:00">July
                                        10, 1940—3 p.m.</date>
                                    <lb/> [Received July 10—1:58 p.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>67. In the event of war between Great Britain and France for which
                                preparations are being made, our two British clerks are apprehensive
                                of internment. I shall resist such a measure on the ground of our
                                extraterritoriality in accordance with the views of Mr. Blake.<note n="38" xml:id="d746fn38">Maxwell Blake, Diplomatic Agent and
                                    Consul General at Tangier.</note> But I should appreciate
                                instructions.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Goold</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>